<br>
However, fundamentally, I think companies are obligated to do what is profitable for them so long as it is within the law.  Also, I think that it helps America as well as hurts it.  Say that these companies do not seek out cheap labor.  Then they cannot compete in the global marketplace with those companies that do, and they go out of business.  That means that all American companies will go out of business.  People's 401k's and other assets will plummet in value.  The negative effects are huge.<br>
<br>
